      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">8. Style busy panes and rely on built-in autofocus</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>During an enhanced request, HET:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>sets <code>aria-busy=&quot;true&quot;</code> on the target pane</li>
          <li>adds a busy CSS class</li>
          <li>disables interactive controls inside the target pane</li>
          <li>removes those markers when the request ends or is aborted</li>
        </ul>
        <p>After content is swapped in, HET focuses the first <code>[autofocus]</code> in the inserted content and removes that attribute so it does not trigger again.</p>
        <p>Relevant reference:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/requests#ui-feedback-while-requests-are-in-flight">UI feedback while requests are in flight</a></li>
          <li><a href="reference/api#busyclass"><code>busyClass</code></a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

